               <p>625. <persName id="def1-625-18600709" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-625-18600709" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-625-18600709" type="age" value="26"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-625-18600709" type="surname" value="ANDERSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-625-18600709" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">JOHN ANDERSON</hi> (26)</persName>
                  <rs id="t18600709-625-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18600709-625-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18600709-625-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>, Stealing 1 watch, Value 3<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. the property of <persName id="t18600709-name-170" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18600709-name-170" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18600709-name-170" type="surname" value="GROOM"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18600709-name-170" type="given" value="EMMA"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18600709-625-offence-1 t18600709-name-170"></join>Emma Groom</persName>, from her person.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. DICKIE</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18600709-name-171" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18600709-name-171" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18600709-name-171" type="surname" value="GROOM"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18600709-name-171" type="given" value="EMMA"></interp>EMMA GROOM</persName>
                  </hi>. On 15th June I was on a steamboat at London-bridge—the prisoner pushed against me; there was no one else very near me—I heard the click of my watch, and I immediately missed it—I had seen my watch ehortly before, it was tied to a guard which was round my neck—I took hold of the prisoner and a witness came up with my watch in his hand—this is it—I gave 3<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. for it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BROOKE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Where were you? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I was going towards the gangway—I was at the top of the cabin stairs—the prisoner was on my left side—I missed my watch and saw it again when it was pro<lb></lb>duced to me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18600709-name-172" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18600709-name-172" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18600709-name-172" type="surname" value="VEAL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18600709-name-172" type="given" value="ABRAHAM"></interp>ABRAHAM VEAL</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a lighterman employed on board a steamboat running to and from London-bridge—on 15th June 1 was on board and saw Emma Groom, she had hold of the prisoner—I found this watch on the deck close to the prisoner's feet.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="186007090050"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Were there many persons on board? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Eighteen or twenty—they were passing from the gangway—the watch was about two yards from the gangway—a great many people had passed it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18600709-name-173" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18600709-name-173" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18600709-name-173" type="surname" value="BRETT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18600709-name-173" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN BRETT</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">City-policeman</hi>, 443). The prisoner was given into my custody on the afternoon of 15th June, at the Old Swan Pier, on a charge of stealing a watch from a lady—the last witness gave me this watch—I took the prisoner to the station—he gave me an address and I went to several places and he was not known—he gave the address North-street, Commercial-road—I went to three places and could not find it.</p>
               <p>
